{"summary":"Network interface.","description":"<p> </p><p>This module provides an API for the network interface.</p> <div class=\"note\"><div class=\"label\">Note</div><div class=\"content\"><p> </p><p>There is currently <strong>no</strong> support for Windows. </p> <p></p></div></div> <div class=\"note\"><div class=\"label\">Note</div><div class=\"content\"><p> </p><p>The content of this file is <strong>only</strong> valid if the system has been built with &apos;socket&apos; (esock) support, which is the default. </p> <p></p></div></div> <p></p>","funcs":" <a name=\"gethostname-0\"></a><table class=\"func-table\"><tbody><tr class=\"func-tr\"><td class=\"func-td\"><div class=\"bold_code func-head\" ><span id=\"ghlink-gethostname-0-id218510\" class=\"ghlink\"><a href=\"/erldoc/docs/https://github.com/erlang/otp/edit/maint/lib/kernel/doc/src/net.xml#L124\" title=\"Found an issue with the documentation? Fix it by clicking here!\"><span class=\"pencil\"></span></a></span>gethostname() -&gt; {ok, HostName} | {error, Reason}</div></td><td class=\"func-since-td\"></td></tr></tbody></table><div class=\"REFBODY fun-types\"><h3 class=\"func-types-title\">Types</h3><div class=\"REFTYPES rt-1\"><span class=\"bold_code bc-2\">HostName = string()</span></div><div class=\"REFTYPES rt-1\"><span class=\"bold_code bc-2\">Reason = term()</span></div></div><div class=\"REFBODY rb-7\"><p> </p><p>Returns the name of the current host.</p> <p></p></div> <a name=\"getnameinfo-1\"></a><table class=\"func-table\"><tbody><tr class=\"func-tr\"><td class=\"func-td\"><div class=\"bold_code func-head\" ><span id=\"ghlink-getnameinfo-1-id218527\" class=\"ghlink\"><a href=\"/erldoc/docs/https://github.com/erlang/otp/edit/maint/lib/kernel/doc/src/net.xml#L132\" title=\"Found an issue with the documentation? Fix it by clicking here!\"><span class=\"pencil\"></span></a></span>getnameinfo(SockAddr) -&gt; {ok, Info} | {error, Reason}</div></td><td class=\"func-since-td\"><span class=\"since\">OTP 22.0</s